---
Syntax: bond track <edge|guard|keen|spirit>
        bond track <name> confirm  - Switch tracks (resets rank!)
        bond tracks                - List all tracks

There are four bond tracks, each emphasizing a different combat role.
Choose a track with 'bond track <name>'. Once chosen, spend bond points
with 'bond rankup' to advance through 5 ranks.

  Edge   - The path of destruction.
           Increases damroll and raw weapon damage.
           Scaled by weapon base level.
           Mastery: blade lashes out with bonus slash attacks in combat.

  Guard  - The path of the defender.
           Adds armor class (scales with base level) and parry (flat).
           Mastery: blade projects a damage-absorbing ward, periodically
           healing the wielder during combat.

  Keen   - The path of precision.
           Increases hitroll (scaled), critical chance and critical
           multiplier (flat bonuses per rank).
           Mastery: strikes inflict bleeding wounds on foes.

  Spirit - The path of endurance.
           Increases hit points and spellpower.
           Scaled by weapon base level.
           Mastery: weapon periodically restores HP and mana.

Rank costs (bond points):
  Rank 1:    0 (free on track selection)
  Rank 2:  125
  Rank 3:  375
  Rank 4:  750
  Rank 5: 1500

WARNING: Switching tracks resets rank to 1 and forfeits all invested
bond points. Use 'bond track <name> confirm' to confirm a switch.

See also: bond bond mastery
